== 1. Graduate / Junior Risk Analyst

=== Hierarchy Level
0-2 years of experience, entry-level role after completing university (typically finance, mathematics, statistics, engineering, or economics)

=== Key Activities and Responsibilities

*Risk Calculation & Reporting (40-50%):*
- Calculating daily VaR (Value-at-Risk) for trading desks using historical simulation, parametric, or Monte Carlo methods
- Computing risk sensitivities (delta, gamma, vega, theta) for options portfolios
- Running stress tests and scenario analyses on trading positions
- Producing daily risk reports showing VaR, stress losses, limit utilization
- Calculating regulatory capital requirements under Basel III framework
- Monitoring intraday risk metrics and alerting senior risk managers to breaches

*Limit Monitoring (25-30%):*
- Tracking trading positions against approved risk limits (VaR limits, position limits, loss limits)
- Investigating and documenting limit breaches
- Coordinating with traders on limit breach resolutions
- Maintaining limit database and tracking approved limit changes
- Monitoring concentration risk (single issuer, sector, country exposures)
- Producing limit utilization dashboards for management

*Data Management & Systems (15-20%):*
- Extracting position data from trading systems and data warehouses
- Reconciling risk positions with middle office and finance
- Maintaining risk databases and data quality
- Building and updating Excel and Python tools for risk analysis
- Testing and implementing risk system upgrades
- Documenting data sources, calculations, and methodologies

*Model Validation Support (10-15%):*
- Backtesting VaR models (comparing predicted vs actual losses)
- Testing pricing model outputs against market quotes
- Reviewing quant model documentation and assumptions
- Supporting independent model validation team with analysis
- Maintaining model performance metrics and validation schedules

*Ad-hoc Analysis (5-10%):*
- Investigating unusual P&L moves or risk metric changes
- Analyzing impact of market events on portfolio risk
- Supporting regulatory examinations and audit requests
- Researching new risk methodologies and best practices

=== Required Skills

*Technical:*
- Strong quantitative skills (statistics, probability, calculus, linear algebra)
- Programming ability (Python essential, R useful, VBA helpful)
- Excel proficiency (pivot tables, complex formulas, data analysis)
- Understanding of financial instruments (bonds, derivatives, FX, equities)
- Knowledge of risk metrics (VaR, Greeks, stress testing, PV01, DV01)
- Familiarity with risk systems (Murex, Summit, Calypso, Bloomberg MARS)
- Basic understanding of Basel III capital framework

*Interpersonal:*
- Attention to detail and accuracy (risk calculations must be precise)
- Clear communication of technical concepts to non-specialists
- Professional skepticism (challenging traders when appropriate)
- Time management under daily deadline pressure (morning risk report due by 8am)
- Team collaboration with traders, quants, middle office
- Intellectual curiosity about markets and risk management

*Regulatory:*
- Understanding of APRA prudential standards (APS 115, 116, 117, 180)
- Knowledge of Basel III market risk framework
- Awareness of FRTB (Fundamental Review of Trading Book) implementation
- Familiarity with market risk governance and three lines of defense model

