== 3. Market Risk Manager

=== Hierarchy Level
5-8 years of experience, managing risk team and partnering with senior trading leadership

=== Key Responsibilities
- Leading market risk team (3-8 people depending on firm size)
- Owning risk appetite framework for trading division
- Primary interface with trading heads and CRO
- Leading APRA examinations and regulatory relationship
- Designing stress testing and scenario analysis framework
- Approving limit changes and new product risk assessments
- Reporting to board risk committee on trading risks
- Managing model risk governance for trading models

=== Key Skills
Risk managers combine technical risk expertise with leadership capabilities, commercial judgment (understanding trading economics and strategy), executive presence (presenting to C-suite and board), and regulatory relationship management (engaging with APRA, demonstrating sound risk governance).

=== Typical Work Patterns
Work focuses on stakeholder management (40-45%), strategic risk oversight (25-30%), and team leadership (20-25%), with less hands-on calculations (10-15%). Daily interaction with trading heads, presenting to CRO and board, managing regulatory examinations, setting strategic risk direction.

=== Career Progression
*Within 3-5 years*: Head of Market Risk for entire markets division, Chief Risk Officer (smaller bank), or Head of Model Risk Management / Model Validation.

