== Australian Market Context

=== Regulatory Environment

Market risk management in Australia governed by:

- *APRA Prudential Standards*: APS 115 (Capital Adequacy: Model Governance), APS 116/180 (Market Risk Capital), APS 117 (Capital Adequacy: Interest Rate Risk in Banking Book)
- *Basel III Framework*: Market risk framework including VaR, stressed VaR, IRC, CRM
- *FRTB (Fundamental Review of Trading Book)*: New market risk framework being implemented, requires more sophisticated risk measurement
- *ASIC Market Integrity Rules*: Trading conduct and market manipulation prevention

=== Compensation Expectations (Australian Banks & Securities Firms)

*Junior Risk Analyst (0-2 years)*: AU\$70,000 - AU\$100,000 base + AU\$10,000-25,000 bonus

*Risk Analyst (2-5 years)*: AU\$100,000 - AU\$140,000 base + AU\$20,000-40,000 bonus

*Senior Risk Analyst (5-8 years)*: AU\$140,000 - AU\$190,000 base + AU\$35,000-65,000 bonus

*Market Risk Manager (8-12 years)*: AU\$180,000 - AU\$270,000 base + AU\$60,000-120,000 bonus

*Head of Market Risk (12+ years)*: AU\$250,000 - AU\$400,000+ base + AU\$100,000-250,000+ bonus

_Note: Compensation ~60-70% of equivalent front office trading roles but significantly better work-life balance. Risk roles offer stable career progression, strong exit opportunities, and valuable regulatory expertise. Major banks (CBA, NAB, ANZ, Westpac, Macquarie) pay at higher end of ranges._

