== Conclusion

Risk management roles in Sales & Trading offer intellectually challenging work combining quantitative analysis, market knowledge, and business partnership. The role provides exposure to trading strategies and markets while maintaining better work-life balance than front office trading positions.

Risk managers play critical role in financial stability - preventing excessive risk-taking, ensuring robust governance, and protecting institutions from catastrophic losses. The 2008 financial crisis and subsequent regulatory reforms have elevated importance and influence of risk management function.

For quantitatively-strong students interested in markets who value analytical rigor, independent thinking, and sustainable career trajectory, risk management in trading environments provides rewarding pathway combining technical challenge with business impact.
